INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '3bce7516-7c1c-406b-ae96-3c1a1fe7dd39',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$gdscript — Understanding Signals and Connections$escape$,
  $escape$gdscript's signal system allows for loose coupling between nodes. The `connect()` function is used to establish a connection between a signal and a callback function. When a signal is emitted, all connected callbacks are invoked. Signals can be defined using the `signal` keyword, and callbacks can be connected using the `connect()` function. This system enables event-driven programming and makes it easy to respond to user input, network events, or other game-related events. For example, a button's `pressed` signal can be connected to a callback function that performs an action when the button is pressed.$escape$,
  $escape$signal player_died
func _on_player_died():
    print('Player died')
    $Button.connect('pressed', self, '_on_player_died')$escape$,
  $escape$gdscript$escape$,
