INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'a99375f3-a70e-4f80-bafd-32ef3e1aa7e7',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$gdscript — Understanding Yield and Async in Godot$escape$,
  $escape$Godot's gdscript provides a built-in way to handle asynchronous operations using the yield keyword. This allows for cooperative multitasking, where a function yields control back to the engine at specific points, enabling other functions to run. However, gdscript also supports async/await syntax for more complex asynchronous operations. To use async/await, you need to define a function with the async keyword and use the await keyword to wait for a promise to resolve. Be cautious of performance pitfalls, such as excessive yielding or awaiting, which can lead to decreased frame rates.$escape$,
  $escape$async func load_level():
    var loader = ResourceLoader.load_interactive("res://levels/level1.tscn")
    while loader.get_resource() == null:
        loader.poll()
        await get_tree().create_timer(0.01)
    var level = loader.get_resource()
    add_child(level)$escape$,
  $escape$gdscript$escape$,
